&lt;/a>
&lt;/h4>&lt;p>By default, the calibration plots include a RUGs layer at the top and at the bottom of the visualization. They are meant to give us an idea of the density of events and non-events as the probabilities progress from 0 to 1.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">
&lt;p>&lt;img src="figs/unnamed-chunk-14-1.png" alt="Calibration plot with arrows pointing to where the RUGS plots are placed in the graph" width="700px" style="display: block; margin: auto;" />&lt;/p>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>This layer can be removed by setting &lt;code>include_rug&lt;/code> to &lt;code>FALSE&lt;/code>:&lt;/p>
