&lt;/div>
&lt;p>The new plot functions support dplyr groupings. So, to overlay the two groups, we just need to pass &lt;code>source&lt;/code> to
&lt;a href="https://dplyr.tidyverse.org/reference/group_by.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&lt;code>group_by()&lt;/code>&lt;/a>:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">
&lt;pre class='chroma'>&lt;code class='language-r' data-lang='r'>&lt;span>&lt;span class='nv'>combined&lt;/span> &lt;span class='o'>&lt;a href='https://magrittr.tidyverse.org/reference/pipe.html'>%&amp;gt;%&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span> &lt;span class='nf'>&lt;a href='https://dplyr.tidyverse.org/reference/group_by.html'>group_by&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>(&lt;/span>&lt;span class='nv'>source&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>)&lt;/span> &lt;span class='o'>&lt;a href='https://magrittr.tidyverse.org/reference/pipe.html'>%&amp;gt;%&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span> &lt;span class='nf'>&lt;a href='https://probably.tidymodels.org/reference/cal_plot_breaks.html'>cal_plot_breaks&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>(&lt;/span>&lt;span class='nv'>Class&lt;/span>, &lt;span class='nv'>.pred_good&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>)&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="figs/unnamed-chunk-19-1.png" alt="Calibration plot with two overlaying probability trends, one is the original and the second is the model" width="700px" style="display: block; margin: auto;" />&lt;/p>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>If we would like to plot them side by side, we can add
&lt;a href="https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/facet_wrap.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&lt;code>facet_wrap()&lt;/code>&lt;/a> as an additional step of the plot:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">
&lt;pre class='chroma'>&lt;code class='language-r' data-lang='r'>&lt;span>&lt;span class='nv'>combined&lt;/span> &lt;span class='o'>&lt;a href='https://magrittr.tidyverse.org/reference/pipe.html'>%&amp;gt;%&lt;/a>&lt;/span> &lt;/span>
&lt;span> &lt;span class='nf'>&lt;a href='https://dplyr.tidyverse.org/reference/group_by.html'>group_by&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>(&lt;/span>&lt;span class='nv'>source&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>)&lt;/span> &lt;span class='o'>&lt;a href='https://magrittr.tidyverse.org/reference/pipe.html'>%&amp;gt;%&lt;/a>&lt;/span> &lt;/span>
&lt;span> &lt;span class='nf'>&lt;a href='https://probably.tidymodels.org/reference/cal_plot_breaks.html'>cal_plot_breaks&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>(&lt;/span>&lt;span class='nv'>Class&lt;/span>, &lt;span class='nv'>.pred_good&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>)&lt;/span> &lt;span class='o'>+&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span> &lt;span class='nf'>&lt;a href='https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/facet_wrap.html'>facet_wrap&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>(&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>~&lt;/span>&lt;span class='nv'>source&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>)&lt;/span> &lt;span class='o'>+&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span> &lt;span class='nf'>&lt;a href='https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/theme.html'>theme&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>(&lt;/span>legend.position &lt;span class='o'>=&lt;/span> &lt;span class='s'>"none"&lt;/span>&lt;span class='o'>)&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="figs/unnamed-chunk-20-1.png" alt="Calibration plot with two side-by-side probability trends" width="700px" style="display: block; margin: auto;" />&lt;/p>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>Our goal in the future is to provide calibration functions that create the models, and provide an easy way to visualize them.&lt;/p>
